+---------------------------% TSO/E-Mail Tutorial +-----------------------------
%Command ===>_zcmd
`
`      The¬SORT`command will sort the entries in the table using the specified
`      field name as the sort key or display a selection panel to prompt for
`      the field(s) to sort by.
`
`      Syntax: ¬SORT field-name direction
`
`      Note:  - field-name must be specified and must be one of the supported
`               names documented below¬or`if blank will cause a selection
`               panel to be displayed.
`             - direction is¬A`for ascending or¬D`for descending (default=A).
`
`      Supported field-names:
`
¬      FROMNODE  `Sending Node Name       ¬DATE      `Date the message received
¬      FROMUSER  `Sending User ID         ¬TIME      `Time the message received
¬      TONODE    `Receiving Node Name     ¬ACTION    `Last action performed
¬      TOUSER    `Receiving User ID
)End
